---
title: Chicken & Sun-Dried Tomato Panini with Zucchini, Mozzarella, Parsley Sauce & Roasted Potato Wedges
description: Somewhere along the line, sandwiches were deemed lunch food only. Yet sandwiches (better yet, panini) could not be more dinner-worthy. Case in point: these panini! Sautéed zucchini, sun-dried tomatoes, melty mozz, and creamy parsley sauce are layered between ciabatta bread then pan-pressed to crispy, golden perfection. Roasted potato wedges complete the meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6422fa0c75a3b77238085f63-c2f17bcd.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65ba9560f6debb5c45b6b865.pdf
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
cuisine: Italian
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 1110 kcal
  fat: 55 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 84 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 51 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1430 mg
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-and-sun-dried-tomato-panini-65ba9560f6debb5c45b6b865
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large
drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, trim and cut @zucchini{1} crosswise into ¼-inch-thick rounds.
Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Halve @ciabatta bread{2}. Finely chop
@sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%ounce}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook chicken until browned and cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Toss zucchini in a #medium bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, half the
@garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add zucchini in a single
layer; cook until golden brown and just tender, ~{2-4%minutes} per side. Turn off
heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp},
parsley, and remaining @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Spread a layer of creamy parsley sauce onto cut sides of ciabattas.

Fill ciabattas with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, sun-dried tomatoes, and a few
slices of zucchini. Slice chicken against the grain; add to ciabattas along with
mozzarella.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for zucchini over medium heat. Once hot, add
sandwiches; press down with a #spatula{}. Cook, pressing occasionally, until bread
is toasted and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If pan seems dry when flipping sandwiches, add another drizzle of oil or ½ tbsp
butter. Lower heat if bread browns too quickly.

Transfer panini to a cutting board. Once cool enough to handle, halve on a diagonal.

Divide between plates and serve with potato wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.